properties.scriptBody:
# This script runs on the UrbanCode generic agent with the agent account having a sudo Docker rule.
set -eux -o pipefail

# Log out of all registries.
logout()
{
	set +e

	echo "Logging out of the registry."
	${fakeRunEcho}$DOCKER_CMD logout ${DOCKER_STAGING_REGISTRY}

	set -e
}

# Clean up files.
cleanup()
{
	set +e

	echo "Cleaning up files."
	rm -f UCProcess.props

	set -e
}

# Set up error trapping to clean up files.
trap cleanup 0 1 2 3 6 15
 
fakeRun=${p:abcActionFakeRun}
fakeFail=${p:abcActionFakeFail}

if [ "$fakeFail" == "true" ]
then
	echo "Is Fake Failure"
	exit 1
fi

fakeRunEcho=
if [ "$fakeRun" == "true" ]
then
	echo "Is Fake Run"
	fakeRunEcho="echo "
fi

PROCESSDIR=`pwd`
DOCKER_WORKDIR=/opt/ucdagent/var/work

DOCKER_STAGING_REGISTRY='${p:abcDockerStagingRegistry}'
DOCKER_STAGING_REGISTRY_USERID='${p:abcDockerStagingRegistryROUserId}'
DOCKER_STAGING_REGISTRY_USERPW='${p:abcDockerStagingRegistryROUserPw}'
DOCKER_IMAGE="${p:Create UCProcess.props File/abcUtilImageName}"
DOCKER_CMD="sudo -n /usr/bin/docker"

echo "Pulling the Provider Docker image [$DOCKER_IMAGE]."
set +e
if [ "$fakeRun" == "true" ]
then
    echo "Fake run doesn't pull the docker image."
else
	# Set up error trapping to logout.
	trap logout 0 1 2 3 6 15

	echo "Logging into the staging registry."
	echo "${DOCKER_STAGING_REGISTRY_USERPW}" | ${fakeRunEcho}$DOCKER_CMD login "${DOCKER_STAGING_REGISTRY}" --username "${DOCKER_STAGING_REGISTRY_USERID}" --password-stdin
	
    echo "Pulling Docker image ${DOCKER_IMAGE}."
	${fakeRunEcho}$DOCKER_CMD pull "${DOCKER_IMAGE}"
fi

set -e

echo
echo "--- Contents of the Temporary Directory $PROCESSDIR Before Processing ---"
ls -laR "$PROCESSDIR"

echo
echo "--- Running the Provider Action ---"
${fakeRunEcho}$DOCKER_CMD run --rm --privileged --network host --user $(id -u):$(id -g) -v /opt/cst:/etc/ssl/certs -v "$PROCESSDIR":"$DOCKER_WORKDIR" "$DOCKER_IMAGE"

echo "--- Echo the Deployment ID ---"
if [ "$fakeRun" == "true" ]
then
    mkdir -p UCProcess.cache/test
    touch UCProcess.cache/test/file.txt
fi

echo "--- Contents of the Temporary Directory $PROCESSDIR After Processing ---"
ls -laR "$PROCESSDIR"

echo "DONE"

cachedAuthTokenRestriction.description: Used by default for any plugin steps without a specified token restriction

properties.scriptBody:
String resPath="${p:resource.path}"

List<String> resPathSegments = resPath.split("/")
String envType = resPathSegments[3]
String provider = resPathSegments[4]
String suite = resPathSegments[5]
String instance = resPathSegments[6]

println "envType=[$envType] provider=[$provider] suite=[$suite] instance=[$instance]"

// Resource path of configuration information resource.
String targetInfoResPath = "/ABC/Management/Lists/Instances/$envType/$provider/$suite/$instance"
println "targetInfoResPath=$targetInfoResPath"

// Resource path of component resource.
String compResPath = "/ABC/Instances/$envType/$provider/$suite/$instance/${p:application.name}/${p:component.name}"
println "compResPath=$compResPath"

outProps.put("abcEnvType", envType)
outProps.put("abcProvider", provider)
outProps.put("abcSuite", suite)
outProps.put("abcInstance", instance)
outProps.put("abcTargetInfoResPath", targetInfoResPath)
outProps.put("abcCompResPath", compResPath)

processes.name: Run UCProcess Script
processes.description: Run the component's UCProcess script.

edges.to: Get ABC Cluster Application Resource Path

edges.from: Get ABC Cluster Application Resource Path

offsets.name: Get ABC Cluster Application Resource Path

properties.scriptBody:
set -e

# Properties from UC process
APPID="${p:Get Resource Property-abcAppId/abcAppId}"
WRAPPERNAME=UCProcessWrapper.sh
WRAPPERSCRIPT="${p:resource/system/work.dir}/ABCDeploy/$WRAPPERNAME"
REQUESTDIR="${p:resource/work.dir}/ABCDeploy/${p:parentRequest.id}"

uname -a
pwd

fakeRun=${p:abcManagementFakeRun}
fakeRunEcho=
if [ "$fakeRun" == "true" ]
then
	echo "Is Fake Run"
	fakeRunEcho="echo "
fi

echo "Request Directory=$REQUESTDIR"
if [ ! -f UCProcess.props ]
then
	echo "ERROR: UCProcess.props file is missing."
	exit 1
fi

if [ -f UCProcess.sh ]
then
	if [ "$APPID" == "" ]
	then
		echo "--- Running UCProcess.sh Script as UCD Agent Account ---"
		${fakeRunEcho}sh UCProcess.sh Deploy
	else
		# Opening up permissions on the downloaded files so that the sudo'd UCProcess.sh script will be able to read them.
		echo
		echo "--- Changing file permissions $REQUESTDIR ---"
		chmod -R o+rX "$REQUESTDIR"
		ls -laR "$REQUESTDIR"
				
		chmod 755 "$WRAPPERSCRIPT"

		# Get the script return code but don't fail if the script fails
		set +e
		echo
		echo "--- Showing the current agent account that will run the sudo command ---"
		id
		echo
		echo "--- Showing the sudo command that will be run ---"
		echo "sudo -u $APPID $WRAPPERSCRIPT"

		echo
		echo "--- Showing the sudo rules set up for the agent account to run $WRAPPERNAME as application account [$APPID] ---"
		sudo -l | grep "$WRAPPERNAME" | grep "$APPID" 2>&1

		echo
		echo "--- Running the sudo command ---"
		${fakeRunEcho}sudo -u $APPID "$WRAPPERSCRIPT" 2>&1
		SCRIPTRETURN=$?
		echo "SCRIPTRETURN=$SCRIPTRETURN"
		set -e

		echo
		echo "--- Changing file permissions $REQUESTDIR ---"
		chmod -R o-rX "$REQUESTDIR"

		# Now fail if the script call had failed
		if [ $SCRIPTRETURN -ne 0 ]
		then
			exit 1
		fi
	fi
else
	echo
	echo "--- No UCProcess.sh Script Found to Run ---"
fi

echo "DONE"
